-- Draghi Says Banks’ ECB Bids Correlate With Bank Bonds
-- B y   J o h n   F r a h e r
-- 2012-01-27T14:27:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-27/draghi-says-banks-ecb-bidding-correlates-with-bond-rollovers.html
(Corrects to specify bank bonds instead of government
bonds in first paragraph.)  European Central Bank President
 Mario Draghi  said ECB analysis of its three-year cash offerings
shows there is a correlation between how much institutions bid
and the amount of bank bonds due to mature.  Draghi made the comments at the  World Economic Forum ’s
annual meeting in Davos,  Switzerland .  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Fraher in Davos, Switzerland at 
 jfraher@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at 
 cstirling1@bloomberg.net  